data.translation: The small electric car is not as rounded as a Fiat 500e or a Mini; instead, it almost resembles a small SUV. This is also due to the upright windshield. data.text: Die Moseltalbrücke ist 935 Meter lang. Da die Brücke Spannweiten von bis zu 218 Metern zwischen den Pfeilern und Widerlagern hat, hat besonders der Güterverkehr einen großen Einfluss auf die Verformungen des Überbaus. Die im Jahr 1972 erbaute Moseltalbrücke trägt täglich rund 37.000 Fahrzeuge, von denen ein Drittel dem Güterverkehr zuzuordnen ist. Im Februar 2023 wurde eine Rissbildung an den Schweißnähten im Brückenkörper festgestellt. Die Ergebnisse der Hauptprüfung werden in bevorstehende Instandsetzungsarbeiten einfließen, die im Laufe des Jahres 2024 beginnen sollen. Aktuell wird die Brücke durch Tempolimits entlastet.
data.translation: The Moselle Valley Bridge is 935 meters long. With spans of up to 218 meters between the pylons and abutments, the freight traffic in particular has a significant impact on the deformations of the superstructure. Built in 1972, the Moselle Valley Bridge carries around 37,000 vehicles daily, a third of which are attributable to freight traffic. In February 2023, cracking was detected in the welds of the bridge body. The results of the main inspection will be incorporated into upcoming repair works, which are set to begin over the course of 2024. Currently, the bridge is being relieved by speed limits.

Trotz Aufladung hält Lamborghini dabei an seinem Hochdrehzahlkonzept fest. Der aufgeladene Achtzylinder entwickelt eine spezifische Leistung von 147 kW / 200 PS pro Liter Hubraum. Die Spitzenleistung von 800 PS gibt der V8-Biturbo im Bereich von 9000 bis 9750 Umdrehungen pro Minute ab. Bis zu 10.000 Umdrehungen pro Minute dreht der V8-Biturbo hoch. Das schaffen sonst nur Rennwagen.

The peak power of 800 hp is delivered by the V8 Biturbo in the range of 9000 to 9750 revolutions per minute. The V8 Biturbo can rev up to 10,000 revolutions per minute. This is otherwise only achieved by racecars.

data.text: Ein altes Rezept, und es ist nicht das schwierigste, das man machen kann, verlangt 1 Liter bestes weißes Weizenmehl, ¾ Liter heiße Milch, um es zu verbrühen, ½ Liter kalte Milch, um es abzukühlen, bevor man 60 (sechzig) Eigelb hinzufügt, die zu weißem Schaum geschlagen werden, Hefe und, nach dem ersten Aufgehen, noch 3 Liter Mehl, ½ Liter geschmolzene Butter, 1,5 lb Zucker. Der Teig sollte eine Stunde lang geknetet werden, bevor zehn geschlagene Eiweiße, Gewürze, Trockenfrüchte und Nüsse hinzugefügt werden. Nach dem zweiten Aufgehen in den speziellen Formen wurde der Teig im sehr heißen Backofen gebacken, wo die Babas noch aufgehen konnten, manchmal sogar bis fast zu einem Meter hoch. Nach dem Backen waren sie zerbrechlich wie ein Soufflé, deshalb wurden sie in der geschlossenen warmen Stube auf die Kissen gelegt, um langsam abzukühlen, da ein kleinster Ruck oder ein leichter frischer Luftzug sie zum Umfallen bringen konnte.
data.translation: An old recipe, not the most difficult one to make, requires 1 liter of the finest white wheat flour, ¾ liter of hot milk to scald it, ½ liter of cold milk to cool it down before adding 60 (sixty) egg yolks, beaten to a white froth, yeast, and after the first rise, another 3 liters of flour, ½ liter of melted butter, 1.5 lbs of sugar. The dough should be kneaded for an hour before adding ten beaten egg whites, spices, dried fruits, and nuts. After the second rise in special molds, the dough was baked in a very hot oven, where the Babas could still rise, sometimes even up to almost a meter high. After baking, they were as fragile as a soufflé, therefore they were laid on cushions in a warm, closed room to cool down slowly, because the slightest jolt or a light breeze could cause them to collapse.

data.translation: PRINCIPLE NUMBER THREE: GLIDING To get to know the overtones, we use the vowels of everyday speech, since they are formed by the amplification of certain overtones. We use this fact by gliding the vowels into each other, so that we can find the overtones along the way between the vowels. The vowels ooo‐uuu‐üüü‐iii (and vice versa) are particularly suitable for this, as the gliding of these vowel combinations over a stable fundamental tone allows us to find the entire singable overtone scale or natural scale. Since the overtones are already present in the sound, you just need to listen loosely and casually for any changes in the sound as you move from one vowel to the next. Try to glide as smoothly as possible, so that you can really hear how the vowels change. This will allow you to hear the changes in the overtones in your voice. And that is the basis for overtone singing.

To become acquainted with the overtones, the vowels of everyday speech are ideal because they are created through the amplification of specific overtones. We leverage this fact by smoothly transitioning vowels into each other to uncover the overtones as we journey between them. Strive for seamless transitions to accurately perceive how the vowels transform. Lauschen meint, den Klang mit neuen Ohren wahrzunehmen; der Klang als das unbekannte Wesen, mit dem wir (immer wieder) zum allerersten Mal in Kontakt kommen und das so tief wie möglich. Zur Vorbereitung auf das Singen kannst Du dir zum Beispiel die Ohren massieren, um die Durchblutung in ihnen zu fördern, was das Hören unterstützt. Oder Du stellst dir vor, wie deine Ohren wachsen, damit sie sich energetisch ausdehnen und so die feineren und subtileren Anteile des Klanges besser erfassen können.
data.translation: Principle number ONE: LISTENING Since the overtones are already present in the sound of our voice, it's not about generating overtones but about consciously perceiving them! This perception naturally takes place primarily through listening, which means active listening with 100% attention, listening with a single focus on the sound with all its details. Listening means perceiving the sound with new ears; the sound as the unknown entity with which we (again and again) come into contact for the first time and that we perceive as deep as possible. To prepare for singing, you can, for example, massage your ears to promote the circulation in them, which helps with hearing. Or you can imagine that your ears are growing, so that they can energetically expand and thus better capture the finer and subtler aspects of the sound.

data.translation: This kind of fake, i.e. playback, is as old as the business itself. In TV shows, there is almost never a real live performance. It would be too cumbersome to set up the equipment. In small TV studios, the necessary facilities are not available either. Besides, the sound of certain bands is also closely tied to the volume. A Marshall amp, for instance, distorts only at a certain amplitude. Although it is possible to imitate all of this today, rock bands like AC/DC do not do so; they want the real sound. So they also play playback in television. I myself had to do so myself when I was a singer/songwriter, too.
